                      <span>1997-07-26</span>
                    </div>
                    <span><p>Entertaining Mathematical Problems by Martin Gardner is a great book for all ages. This book has over 100 problems in sections ranging from topology to games. Some of the problems are simple to many, but there are some that require thought to do. Answers are included on the back. Any math lover will surely enjoy this book.
<br>Paul Raff (Northwestern_Wildcat@ibm.net</span>
                  
              
